  "title": "Children's Gymnastics/Movement Coach",
  "description": "<p>With over <strong>20 years of trusted brand heritage</strong>, BazGym is one of Singapore’s leading gymnastics and movement education providers, serving children and families across multiple locations. We are looking for <strong>passionate, responsible, and energetic Gymnastics Coaches</strong> to join our growing team.</p><h3>🏅 Your Role</h3><p>As a Gymnastics Coach, you will play a key role in shaping children’s confidence, movement skills, and love for sports.</p><p>Key responsibilities include:</p><ul><li><p>Conducting <strong>safe, engaging, and structured gymnastics classes</strong> for children</p></li><li><p>Delivering lessons in line with <strong>BazGym’s curriculum and teaching standards</strong></p></li><li><p>Ensuring <strong>safety, discipline, and positive learning environments</strong></p></li><li><p>Monitoring student progress and providing constructive feedback</p></li><li><p>Supporting <strong>events, carnivals, and internal programmes</strong> when required</p></li><li><p>Maintaining professionalism and representing the <strong>BazGym brand positively</strong></p></li><li><p>Working closely with Branch Managers and Head of Programmes</p></li></ul><h3>💡 Who We’re Looking For</h3><ul><li><p>Experience in <strong>gymnastics, sports coaching, or physical education</strong> preferred</p></li><li><p>Relevant certifications (or willingness to obtain them)</p></li><li><p>Good communication skills with children and parents</p></li><li><p>Responsible, punctual, and team-oriented</p></li><li><p>Passion for teaching, movement, and child development</p></li><li><p>Fresh graduates with strong attitude are welcome</p></li></ul><h3>🎁 What We Offer</h3><ul><li><p>Competitive salary with <strong>structured progression</strong></p></li><li><p>Training and <strong>skills upgrading opportunities</strong></p></li><li><p>Supportive team and clear teaching framework</p></li><li><p>Stable, long-term career path in a growing organisation</p></li><li><p>Opportunities to participate in company events and programmes</p></li></ul>",
